        .col-xs-12.col-sm-9
          p(itemprop="description") Hi! My name is <span itemprop="name">Caio Ribeiro Pereira</span>, a software engineer from Brazil, my programming's skills is based on understanding this alphabet soup: <em>Node.js, JavaScript, Meteor, Ruby, Rails and front-end stuffs</em>.<br>I'm bachelor in Information Systems, blogger on my free times, <a data-scroll href="#books">author of some tech books</a>, admirer of programming, technology and movies and tv series. Actively engaged in the communities: <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/nodebr" target="_blank" rel="co-worker">NodeBr</a>, <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/devinsantos" target="_blank" rel="co-worker">DevInSantos</a>, <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/meteor-brasil" target="_blank" rel="me">Meteor Brazil</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/javascriptbrazil/" target="_blank" rel="me">JavaScript Brazil</a>.<br>I started as lecturer in 2011 at DevInSantos, Exatec and Fatec events, talking about Node.js, Meteor and JavaScript.<br>I created <a href="https://devfreecasts.github.io" target="_blank" rel="me">DevFreeCasts</a>, <a href="https://devfreebooks.github.io" target="_blank" rel="me">DevFreeBooks</a>, <a href="https://devnewsletters.github.io" target="_blank" rel="me">DevNewsletters</a> and I am moderator of <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/meteor-brasil" target="_blank" rel="me">Meteor Brazil Google groups</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/javascriptbrazil/" target="_blank" rel="me">JavaScript Brazil Facebook group</a>.
